Sec. 13.55.100.   Definitions.
In this chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,
(1) department means the Department of Health;
(2) emancipated minor means a minor whose disabilities have been removed for general purposes under
AS 09.55.590
;
(3) health care provider has the meaning given in
AS 09.65.340
;
(4) hospital has the meaning given in
AS 13.52.268
;
(5) minor means an individual under 18 years of age who is not an emancipated minor;
(6) opioid includes the opium and opiate substances and opium and opiate derivatives listed in
AS 11.71.140
and 11.71.160;
(7) opioid overdose drug has the meaning given in
AS 09.65.340
.
